line: Okay, you see where you’re going? Let’s work on how to get there.
Okay, good...tip down...bow arm out...three fingers-
Why three?
‘Cause two’s not enough and four’s too much-
You guys want mustard or mayo, or both?
Who puts mayo on a hot dog?
We’ll both have mustard, hon!  Okay.  Draw back, deep breath...
Good job, Hawkeye.  Go get your arrow.
Enough murder practice!  Soup’s on!
One sec, babe.  Be right there! We’re gonna kill some hot dogs. We’re hungry.
Lila?  Babe, did you see Lila-
Guys?  Guys, come on...
Laura?
LAURA!
Good sport.  Have fun?
It was fun.
This thing on?  Hey, Ms. Potts. Pep.  If you find this recording, don’t post it on social media. It’s going to be a real tearjerker.
I don’t know if you’re ever going to see these.  I don’t even know if you’re still...God, I hope so. Today’s day twenty-one, no...twenty- two.

You know, if it wasn’t for the existential terror of staring into the literal void of space, I’d say I’m feeling a little better today. Infection’s run its course, thanks to the Blue Meanie back there. You’d like her.  She’s very practical.  And only a tiny bit sadistic.
The fuel cells were cracked during battle, but we figured out a way to reverse the ion charge.  Bought ourselves about 48 hours of flight time.  Problem is that was about...49 hours ago.
Which means, we’re dead in the water.  A thousand light years from the nearest 7-11.
Most of the quote-unquote ‘food’ and potable water ran out two weeks ago.
Pep, I know I said no more surprises.  But, I gotta say, I was really hoping to pull off one last one.  But it looks like...well, you know what it looks like.

Don’t feel bad about this.  I mean, actually, if you grovel for a couple weeks, and then move on with enormous guilt...I should probably lie down for a minute, rest my eyes.  Please know, when I drift off, it will be like every day lately.  I’m fine, totally fine. I’m going to dream about you.  It’s always you.
I couldn’t stop him.
Neither could we.
I lost the kid.
We...lost...
Is Pepper...?
Stay here, you stay right here-
I’m not going anywhere.
It’s been twenty-three days since Thanos came to Earth.
World governments are in pieces, as you can imagine.  But the parts that still work are trying to take a census.  It looks like he did what he said he was going to do.
Thanos wiped out fifty percent of all the living creatures on Earth.
Not just Earth.
You sure about that?
You never have to ask me that.
Where is he now?
We don’t know.  He just opened a portal and walked through.
What’s his deal?
He’s pissed.
He thinks he failed.  Which, of course, he did.  But there’s a lot of that going around, ain’t there?
Until this second, I literally thought you were a Build-a-Bear.
We’ve been hunting Thanos for three weeks - deep space scans, satellites - we got nothing.  Tony, you fought him-
Who told you that?  I didn’t fight him, he wiped my face with a planet while a Bleecker Street magician gave away the store.  There was no fight because he’s not beatable.
Did he give you anything to go on? Clues, coordinates-
I saw this coming, few years back. Didn’t wanna believe.  I thought I was dreaming...
Tony, I need you to focus-
And I needed you, as in past tense. That trumps what you need.  It’s too late, buddy.  You know what I need?

I need a shave and a burger, not a bowl of soup. And I believe I remember telling all of you, alive and otherwise, that we needed a suit of armor around the world, whether it impacted our precious freedoms or not-
But that didn’t work out, did it?

I said we’d lose, you said we’d “do that together, too.”  Guess what, Cap, we lost, and you weren’t there.  But that’s what we do, right?  Our best work after the fact?  We’re the “Avengers”, not the “Pre-vengers-”
Tony, take it easy...
I’ve got nothing for ya, Cap.  No coordinates, no clues, no strategies, no options.  Zero, zip, nada.  No trust.  Here.  You take this.  You find him, you put this on, and hide.  I’m fine!
Bruce gave him a sedative.  Should be out the rest of the day.
Take care of him.  When I come back, I’ll bring a bottle of Xorrian elixir.
Where are you going?
To kill Thanos.
Hey, hey, hang on.  We’re sort of a team here.  Between you and me, morale’s a little fragile.
Oh, I’m sorry.  My fault.
All right, team!  I’m going to go kill Thanos.  Message me if you get any intel that can help. Otherwise, I’ll report back when he’s dead.  Great work, everybody.
Look, we realize “up there’s” more your territory, but this is our fight, too.
Do you even know where he is?
I know people who might-
Don’t bother.
I can tell you where Thanos is.

Thanos spent a long time trying to...perfect me.  When he worked, he talked.  About his Great Plan. Even disassembled, I wanted to please him.  I’d ask, where would we go once his plan was complete? His answer was always the same: “To the Garden.”
You’re saying Thanos had a retirement plan.
Where’s this garden?
When Thanos snapped his fingers, Earth become ground zero for a power surge of ridiculously cosmic proportions.  No one’s seen anything like it.
Until two days ago.
You’re saying he snapped his fingers again.  Where?
Planet is unnamed, but inhabitable. Rich atmosphere, good soil-
A garden.
Thanos is there.  And he just used the stones.
You know, we’d be going short- handed.
Because he killed all our friends.
Are we saying they’re dead?  We’re using that word now?
He’s still got the stones.
So, we take them.  And we use them to bring everybody back.
Just like that?
Yeah.  Just like that.
If there’s even the smallest chance we can undo this, then we owe it to everyone who’s not sitting here to try.
If we do this...why would it end any differently than it did before?
Because before you didn’t have me.
Hey, new girl.  All of us in here are about that superhero life. Where’ve you been all this time?
There’s a lot of people in the universe.  And they didn’t all have you.
I like this one.
Let’s go get that son of a bitch.
Trust me.  You get used to it.
Okay, who here hasn’t been to space?
Oh, you’re gonna hate this.
Approaching jump in three, two...
I’ll head down for recon.  If I’m not back in fifteen, you’ll know I found him.
This is going to work, Steve.
I know it will.  Because I don’t know what I’m going to do if it doesn’t.
No satellites, no ships, no armies. No ground defenses of any kind. It’s just him.
That’s enough.
Where are they?
Answer the question!
The universe required correction. After that, the stones served no purpose beyond temptation.
You murdered trillions.
You should be grateful.
Where are the stones?
Gone.  Reduced to atoms.
You used them two days ago!
I used the stones to destroy the stones.  It nearly killed me. But the work is done.  It always will be.
No...they can’t be gone...
He’s lying.
My father is many things.  A liar is not one of them.
Thank you, daughter.  Perhaps I’ve treated you-
What did you do?
I went for the head.
So, I went on a date the other day.
Good job, Bobby.  Back in the game.
Thank you, Jimmy.  First in five years.  I sat there at dinner thinking, what are we even supposed to talk about?
What did you talk about?
Same old crap.  How much things have changed.  How much we miss the Mets.  My job, his job.  Then it got kind of quiet.  He cried during the salads.
What about you?
I cried just before dessert.  But I’m seeing him again tomorrow. So...

That’s great.  You’ve already done the hardest part.  You took a jump, didn’t know where you’d come down. And that’s it, those little brave baby steps we’ve gotta take.  To try to make us feel whole again, to find a purpose... I went into the ice right after I met the love of my life.  Woke up seventy years later and...had to keep going.
The world’s been left in our hands. If we don’t do something with it...then Thanos might as well have killed all of us.
Hello?
Hey.  Kid.  What happened here?
What?
Cassie!  Cassie!
Dad?
Peanut?
I thought you were gone.
I’m sorry.  I’m back...I’m back...I’m back...
We boarded that “highly suspect warship” Danvers pinged.
And?
It was an infectious garbage scow.
So thanks for the hot tip-
You were closer.
And now we smell like garbage-
You get a reading on those tremors?
Minor subduction in the African plate.
Do we have a visual?  How are you handling it?
Nat.  It was a mild earthquake.  In the ocean.  We handle it by not handling it.
I can have NASA redirect a satellite, do a sweep just to make sure.
Thanks.  Carol, you’re still coming our way next month?
Not likely.
Getting another haircut?

Listen, fur-face, I’m covering a lot of territory out here.  The things that have been happening on Earth have been happening everywhere else.  On thousands of planets.  You might not see me for a long time.
All right.  Everybody keep keeping their eyes open.  This channel’s always active.  Anything goes sideways, anyone makes trouble where they shouldn’t, it comes through me.
What’s up?  Where are you?
Mexico.  Got some news.
Okay...
Federalés found a room full of bodies outside Juarez.  Cartel guys.  Guns still in their pants.
Could be a rival hit-
But it wasn’t.  Same MO as Marseille.  And Kiev.
It’s definitely Barton.
What he’s done here...what he’s been doing...I got to tell you, part of me doesn’t want to find him.
Find out where’s he going next.
I’d offer to cook you dinner but you seem sad enough already.
Come by to do your laundry?
And see a friend.
Your friend’s fine.
She leave the house today?
Nothing out there I particularly want to see.
I spotted a pod of whales coming over the bridge.
In the Hudson.
Fewer ships, cleaner water.  Just saying, there’s still a world out there.
If you’re about to tell me to look on the bright side, I’m about to hit you with a peanut butter sandwich.
Sorry.  Force of habit.
I don’t know how you do it.
I guess I don’t know how not to.
Me, neither.
I keep telling them, move on.  Grow past it.  And some of them actually do.  But not us.
If I move on, who does this?
Maybe it doesn’t need to be done.
I used to have nothing.  Then I got this.  This job, this family.  And I was better because of it.
And even though they’re gone, I’m still trying to be...better.
I think we both need to get a life.
You first.
Hello?  Is anyone home?  This is, uh, Scott Lang?  We met a few years ago.  At the airport?
This an old message?
It’s the front gate.
Scott, are you okay?
What?  Yes.
Have either of you guys ever studied quantum physics?
Only to make conversation.

Well, five years ago, just before this Thanos guy...I went into a place called the Quantum Realm. It’s like its own microscopic universe.  You can only get there if you’re incredibly small.  Hope, she’s my...she was supposed to pull me out.  But then Thanos happened. And I was stuck in there.
I’m sorry.  It must’ve been a long five years.
Okay, but that’s the thing.  It wasn’t.  For me, it was only five hours.  The rules in the Quantum Realm aren’t like out here. They’re completely unpredictable. Is anybody gonna eat that sandwich?
Scott, what are you talking about?
Time works differently in the Quantum Realm.

Problem is, right now, it’s chaos, there’s no way to navigate it.  But what if we could figure out a way to enter the Quantum Realm at a certain point in time...and come out in another.  Like, before Thanos-
Wait...wait.  Scott.  Are you talking about a time machine?
No, not a machine.  More like a... Yeah, like a time machine.  I know it sounds crazy...
Scott, I get emails from a raccoon. Nothing’s crazy anymore.
So, who do we talk to about this?
Morgan H. Stark.  Chow time.  Want some lunch?
Define lunch or be disintegrated.
You should not be wearing that. It’s part of a special anniversary gift I made for Mom.  You thinking about lunch?
Where’d you find this?
Garage.
You like going in the garage?  So does Daddy.  It’s all right.  Mommy never wears what I buy her.
I just want to thank you folks for dropping by.  It’s not every day one gets to contemplate biting it on an inter-dimensional timescape.
You’ve got some objections to the plan.
So you’re calling it a plan.  To me, it sounds like an exotic suicide method.  Not to mention, it’s impossible.
We know what it sounds like.
Tony, after what you’ve seen, is anything really impossible?

Quantum fluctuation kinda messes with the Planck Scale, which then triggers the Deutsch Proposition, can we agree on that? Chai?  In layman’s terms, it means you can cancel your Netflix subscription because you’re not coming home.
I did.
Which was a billion-to-one cosmic fluke.  Now you want to pull a- What are you calling it?
A time heist.
Oh, of course, a time heist, why didn’t we think of this before? Right, because it’s a pipe dream. Who are you again?
Still Scott...
Tony, the Stones exist in the past. We could get them and bring them here.
We can snap our own fingers.  We can bring everybody back.
Or screw it up worse than he already has.
I don’t believe we would.

Gotta say it.  Sometimes I’ve missed that giddy optimism.  Sadly, all your high hopes won’t help me if there’s no logical, tangible way for me to safely execute said “time heist.”  I believe the most likely outcome would be our collective demise.
Not if we strictly follow the rules of time travel.  No talking to our past selves.  No betting on sporting events-
Stop, Scott.  Stop.  Are you telling me that your plan to save the universe is more than loosely based on Back to the Future?
No...
Good.  Because that would be horseshit.  Scientifically speaking, your brother’s picture doesn’t disappear just ‘cause you went to the dance with your mom. That’s not how quantum physics works.
We have to take a stand.
We did stand.  And yet here we are.
Look, Stark-  Can I call you Tony?
Please don’t-
Tony-
Fine.

I get that you’ve got a lot on the line, here.  You’ve got a wife.  A daughter.  But I lost someone very important - a lot of us did - and now we have a chance to save her, and everyone else, and you won’t even-
No, Scott.  I won’t.  Even.
Mommy told me to come save you.
Good job.  I’m saved.  I wish you were coming here to ask me something else.  I’m honestly happy to see you.  If you want to stay-
Tony, I get it.  And I’m happy for you.  I am.  But this is a second chance.
Yeah, well, I got my second chance right here.  I can’t roll the dice on it.  The table is set for six. If you don’t talk shop, you’re welcome to stay for lunch.
He’s scared.
He’s not wrong.
What are we gonna do?  We need him. You want to stop?
No.  I want to do it right. We’re going to need a really big brain.
Bigger than his?
I’m confused.
These are confusing times.
No, that’s not what I’m-
I’m kidding, I get it.  It’s crazy. I wear shirts now!
But why?
Five years ago, we got our asses kicked, right?
He’s heard.
It was worse for me.  Because I lost twice.  First Hulk lost.  Then Banner lost.  Then we all lost.
No one blamed you, Bruce.
I did-  I feel like I’m the only one eating.  Here, try some.
Thing is, I kept thinking, it didn’t have to be that way.  That the best of Banner and best of Hulk, if they’d worked together, maybe they could’ve stopped Thanos.
Okay.  But how did...this happen?
For years I treated the Hulk like a disease, something to get rid of. But when I started treating him like the cure...
Eighteen months in the Gamma Lab. I put the brains and the brawn together.  And now look at me. Best of both worlds.
Mr. Hulk?  Can we get a picture?
100%, little lady.
Thanks, pal.  Hulk out!
So, Bruce, about what we said-
The time travel do-over?  I don’t know, that’s kind of outside my field of expertise...
You pulled this off.  I remember a time that was impossible, too.
I’m supposed to be on Oprah next week, but I guess I could move things around.
Friday, you up?
Yes, sir.
I’ve had a mild inspiration, like to see if it checks out.  I would like to run one last sim before we pack it in for the night.  This time, in the shape of a Mobius Strip, inverted.
Processing. The model forms.
All right, give me the eigenvalue of that particle, factoring in spectral decomp.  Run it.  That’ll take a second.  And don’t worry if it doesn’t pan out, I’m just kind of...
Model rendered.
Shit.
Shit.
What are you doing up?
Shit.
First of all, that’s a Mommy word, she coined it.
Why are you up?
I just had something on my mind.
Was it juice pops?
Correct.  Great minds think alike. What kind do you want?
You done? Now you are.
Tell me a story.
Once upon a time, Maguna went to bed.  The end.
That was a bad story. He runs his hand over her hair.
Love you tons.
Love you three thousand.
Wow, that’s a lot.
Out like a light.  Don’t know how much she loves you but she loves me three thousand.
That’s up there.
What’re you reading?
A book about composting-
I think I solved it.
Just so we’re both talking about the same thing-
Time travel.
That’s amazing.
Yeah.
And terrifying.
To say the least.
We got really lucky-
I know-
Not everybody did.
I can’t help everybody.
Except, it sort of seems like you can.
Not if I stopped right here.
Tony, trying to get you to stop is one of the few failures of my life.
I could just lock the lab, put it in a trunk, sink it to the bottom of the lake, and go to bed.
But could you rest?
You’re sure these modifications are safe?
I reran my calculations three times-
Because the guy who invented this thing is pretty much a genius-
I have seven PhD’s, an MD, the Hans Bethe Award for Physics, and I’m personal friends with Bill Nye the Science Guy.  We’re good.
Yeah.  And you look like that on purpose.
Breakers are set, emergency generator’s on stand-by.
Good.  If we blow the grid, I don’t want to lose Tiny back in the ‘50’s.
Excuse me?
He was kidding.
I was kidding.
You were kidding, right?
Honestly, I have no idea.  We’re attempting time travel.  Either it’s all a joke, or none of it is. We’re good!  Helmet on.
Okay.  I’m going to send you back one week, give you an hour to look around, then bring you back in ten seconds.  Make sense?
Perfectly not confusing.
Good luck, Scott.  You’ve got this.
Yes, I do, Captain America.  Yes, I-
Counting down from three, two, one...
Uh, guys?  This doesn’t feel right.
Is that Scott?
Probably...?
Get him back!
Oh, my back!
Bruce!  Get it under control.  What the hell is going on?
I got it, I know exactly what’s going on.  Pretty much.
Oh, my God.
It’s a baby.
It’s Scott.
As a baby!
When I tell you, kill the power! Now!
Somebody peed my pants.  I don’t know if it was baby-me or old-me. Or just me-me.
Why the long face?  Wild guess, he turned into a baby?
Among other things.
EPR Paradox.  Instead of pushing Lang through time, you were pushing time through Lang.  It’s dangerous. I probably should’ve cautioned you against it.
You did.
Thank god, I’m here.  Regardless, I fixed it.
That is a fully-functioning, time- space GPS.  I just want peace. Resentment is corrosive.  I hate it.
Me, too.
We’ve got a shot at the Stones.  I just need you to know my priorities.  Bring back everyone we lost, hopefully.  Keep what I found, definitely.  And, let’s not die trying.
Sounds like a deal.
But wait, there’s more.   Act now, and it comes with a bonus offer.
Tony, I don’t know-
What’s to know?  He made it for you.  Plus, I gotta get it out of the garage before Morgan takes it sledding.
Thank you, Tony.
Just don’t flaunt it.  I didn’t bring enough for the whole team. We are getting the whole team, right?
We’re trying.
Hey, Humie.  Where’s Big Green?
Um, kitchen, I think.
Rhodey, careful on re-entry. There’s an idiot in the landing zone.
Oh, my God!
What’s up, Regular-Sized Man?
Finally.  I ain’t got all day.
I call shotgun!
What the heck are they looking at?
I’m kind of famous...
Yeah, I’m sure that’s it.  Kind of a step down from golden palaces and magic hammers...
They lost Asgard, then half their people.  Maybe they’re just happy to have a home.
You shouldn’t have come.
Hey, Valkyrie!  Great to see you!
Uh huh.  I liked you better either of the other ways.
This is Rocket.
Hey.
Hey. He won’t see you.
We didn’t say we were here to see-
Great, then you can hose out the gut buckets-
We’re definitely here to see him.
He can’t give you what you need.
It’s that bad?
We only see him once a month.  When he comes in for “supplies.”
Something died in here.
Hello...?  Thor...?
Are you here about the cable?
Cinemax went out two days ago, and the sports are all...fuzzy...
Thor?
BROS!  Bring it in!
Yeah, I’m good.
Hulk, you know my boys, Korg and Miek, right?
Beer’s in the bucket.  Feel free to log on to the WiFi.
Hey, guys.  Long time no-
Thor!  This kid on the TV just called me a dickhead!
Noobmaster again?
NoobMaster69 called me a dickhead-

Noobmaster, this is Thor, again. God of Thunder.  This is your last warning.  Log off this game or I will come to your basement, rip off your arms and shove them up your butt.  Right, who wants a drink?
Hey, buddy, are you all right?
Don’t I look all right?
You look like melted ice cream-
So, what’s up?  Just here for a hang?
We need your help.  There’s a chance we can fix everything.
Like the cable?  It’s driving me bananas.
Like Thanos.
Don’t say that name.
Yeah, we don’t say that name in here.
Please take your hand off me.
Now, I know the thought of...that guy might scare you-
Scared?  Why would I be scared of that guy?  I’m the one who killed that guy, remember?  Anyone else here kill that guy?
Didn’t think so.  Korg, tell everyone who chopped Thanos’ head off.
Stormbreaker?
Not.  Cool.  Man.
Don’t.  Care.  Dude.
Look, I get it.  You’re in a rough patch.  I’ve been there.  But you know who helped me out of it?
Was it Natasha?
It was you.  You helped me.  And I need you to help me again.
Ask the Asgardians down there how much “my help” is worth.
At least they’re alive-
They were gods!  Now they’re fisherpeople!  The ones that are left, anyway.
That’s the thing.  I think we can bring them back.
Stop.  Stop.  I know you think I’m down here, wallowing in my own self- pity, waiting to be rescued.  But I’m fine.  I’m happy.  Whatever it is you’re offering, don’t care. Couldn’t care less.
Come on, pal.  We need you.
There’s beer in the ship.
What kind?
Why are you doing this?  We never did anything to you!
You survived.  Half the planet didn’t.  They got Thanos.  You get me.
You’re done hurting people.
We hurt people?  You’re crazy.
Wait!  Help me!  I’ll give you anything!  What do you want?
What I want...you can’t give me.
You shouldn’t be here.
Neither should you.
I’ve got a job to do.
That what you’re calling this?
Killing these people isn’t going to bring your family back. We found something.  A chance, maybe...
Don’t.
Don’t what?
Give me hope.
I’m just sorry I couldn’t give it sooner.
Out of the way, Lebowski.
Hey, Ratchet, you get lost in there?
It’s Rocket, and shut up.  You’re only a genius on Earth, pal.
And you’re only in there because you have tiny hands.
Fixed it.
Thank you.
Get used to saying that.
Time travel suit, I like it.
Easy, easy.  Careful with those.
I’m being very careful-
You’re being very Hulky-

These are Pym Particles.  You can’t shrink to the Quantum Realm without them, and since Hank Pym got snapped out of existence, we can’t make any more.  I told you.  We’ve only got enough for one round trip each, no do-overs.
Plus two test runs-
One test run. Okay, maybe I’m not ready.
I’m game.
I’ll do it.
Okay, Clint, you might feel a little disoriented when you chronoshift-
Hang on, I’ve got to ask, if we can do this, why don’t we just go find baby Thanos and, you know...
Uh, one, because that’s horrible. And, two, killing baby Thanos doesn’t kill adult Thanos.  Time doesn’t work like that.  You can’t change the future by changing the past.
Sure, we can.  We take the stones before Thanos gets them, then he doesn’t have them.  Problem solved.
That’s not how it works.
I don’t know.  That is kind of what I’ve heard-
Heard from who?
Star Trek.  Terminator.  Bill and Ted’s Excellent-

WHY DOES EVERYONE THINK THIS? THAT’S NOT TRUE.  IF YOU TRAVEL TO THE PAST, THEN THAT PAST HAS BECOME YOUR PRESENT, AND YOUR FORMER PRESENT HAS BECOME THE PAST, WHICH NOW CAN’T BE CHANGED BY YOUR NEW FUTURE!
Exactly.
Excuse me?
Apparently, Back to the Future is bullshit.
Look, are we doing this or not?
Okay, Clint.  Starting in three, two, one...
No.  Not yet...  LILA!
Dad?
Are you all right?  Hey, look at me.  You okay?
Tell me something good...
It worked.  It worked.
Holy crap.  We’re freaking time travelers.
Okay.  Now that we’ve got how, we’re going to need where and when.
Most folks here have encountered at least one of the six Infinity Stones-
I think you mean nearly been killed by one of the six Infinity Stones.
I haven’t. Just...saying.
Regardless, we’ve only got enough Pym Particles for one round trip, each.  And the Stones have been in a lot of places throughout history.
Our history.  Not all of them are going to be a fun drop-in.
Which means we’ve got to pick our targets.
Exactly.  Let’s start with the Aether.  Thor, what do we know?
Is he asleep?
I’m pretty sure he’s dead.
The Aether’s not a stone, it’s more of an angry sludge.  My grandfather hid it from Dark Elves in a rock between dimensions that can only be accessed every 5000 years.
Or...by Jane.  She stuck her hand in a rock.  Then the Aether stuck itself inside her.  Then I took her to Asgard.  We were dating... We’re not anymore.
Quill said he stole the Power Stone from Morag.
That’s a person?
It’s a planet.  Quill was a person.
Wait, like a planet...in space?
Aw, look.  It’s like a puppy, all happy and everything.
You want to go to space, puppy? I’ll take you to space.
Thanos found the Soul Stone on Vormir.
And that is...?
A dominion of death at the very center of celestial existence.  It’s the place where Thanos murdered my sister.
Not it.
So this ‘Time Stone’ guy...what kind of doctor was he?
Strange?

To the right.

To the left.
Right.
Left.

Tonight’s Red-Hot Red Carpet is here at the Walt Disney Concert Hall, where Tony Stark’s third annual benefit for the Firefighter Family Fund has become the go-to charity gala on L.A.’s high-society calendar.  But this great cause is only part of the story--

Oh, no, no... I’m not saying, like, “wedding.”  No, not like that.  I’m just saying, you know...
Can I get you another glass of wine?
A vodka martini, extra dry, with extra olives as soon as possible.
Okay.
And, Tony...
I’m not a cheeseburger.
No.  You’re not a cheeseburger.
Mr. Stark! I was hoping I could get a reaction from you.
How’s panic?
I was referring to your company’s involvement in this latest atrocity.
Hey, they just put my name on the invitations --
Is this what you call accountability?
When were these taken?
Yesterday.  Good P.R. move, you tell the world you’re a changed man, even I believed you.
I didn’t approve this shipment.
Well your company did.
Come with me.
I made some promises I’m not going to be able to keep.  I suggest you pull all your money out of Stark Industries immediately --
Is this like a tick for you? Whenever you have a feeling, you start going to all the people who don’t trust you, who don’t protect you.  They’re going to put a spin on everything you say.

Wait a minute.  I got to ask you something.   I’m dead serious about this.  I’m not kidding.  Am I losing my mind or is Pepper really cute?  Do you think she’s attractive and interesting, or is it just that her hair is down? I’ve been out of the game for a while.
Are you out of your mind.  You’re messing with the “guys in the rooms”, we’re talking about billion dollar interests, the world order --
I’m not worried about that right now --
-- you should be.  You’ll disappear.  I can’t protect you against people like that --?
DO YOU MIND?
Tony don’t be so naive --

-- naive?  I was naive before, when I was growing up and they told me don’t ever cross this line, this is how we do business.  In the meantime we’re double-dealing under the table.  We don’t even deserve to represent the United States --
-- Tony, you’re a child --!
-- you don’t believe I can turn this company around, do you --?
-- you’ve got about as much control over things as a child riding in the backseat of your father’s car with a red plastic steering wheel in your hand.
Maybe I’ll just get out of the car.
You’re not even allowed in the car. I’m the one who’s filing the injunction against you.
It’s the only way I could protect you.
This is going to stop.

-- the ten mile drive to the outskirts of Gulmira can only be described as a descent into Hell, into a modern-day Heart of Darkness.  Simple farmers and herders, from peaceful villages, driven from their homes at the butt of Western rifles and the turrets of modern tanks.  Displaced from their lands by Warlords and insurgent groups emboldened by their newfound power -- a power fueled by high-tech weapons easily purchased with Poppy money on the black market -- and further destabilizing a fragile region which for decades has been a tinderbox of tribal feuding and ethnic hatred --

The villagers have taken shelter in whatever crude dwellings they can find -- in the ruins of other razed villages, in the cold barren scrublands, or in the remnants of an old Soviet smelting plant.  Our translator relayed to us one human tragedy after another.  A seven year old boy, thin as a scarecrow, clutching yellowed photographs and holding them out to anyone who would stop, with a child’s simple question: where are my mother and father?  A woman, begging for news of her husband, who’d been kidnapped by insurgents -- either forced to join their militia, or to be shot without reason --
With no political will or international pressure, there is little hope for these newly-formed refugees.  Refugees who can only wonder one thing: is the world watching?
Are you going to tell me what’s going on?
Get my house in Dubai ready.  I want to throw a party.
Yes.  Mr. Stark.

I’m in the convertible.  Not the best time --

UAV has entered the no-fly zone--
Because I think I’m staring at one right now, and it’s about get blown to Kingdom Come.
Rhodes!  You got something for me?
Uhh...’kingdom come’?
This is my exit -- gotta go.
Ballroom Control -- this is Viper 1 & 2 checking in.  UAV is in sight.

Viper 2 -- he’s on your belly! Shake him!
What--?

I think it’s...a Man, sir.
Son of a bitch.  Tony--!
Still there Viper 2.  ROLL!  ROLL!
Sir: two minutes and there won’t be sufficient power to get home.
I’M HIT!
Viper 2, do you see a chute?
Negative!  No chute, no chute--
Power critical, set course for home immediately.
The UAV is going after him!  It’s attacking--!
GOOD CHUTE!  GOOD CHUTE!  You’re not gonna believe this, Ballroom... but that thing just saved his ass.
Viper 2: re-engage.
-- WAIT --!
-- TAKE THE TARGET OUT!

LOCKED ON!  LOCKED ON!

I got him good.  He went down, he was smokin’.  But I cannot confirm.
Get me home...
Welcome.
Compliments of Tony Stark.

His escape bore unexpected fruit.

The inside of Tony Stark’s mind.
Everything you will need to build this weapon.
Stark has made a masterpiece of death.  A man with a dozen of these could rule from the Pacific to the Ukraine.  And you dream of Stark’s throne -- we have a common enemy.

Civilization, gentlemen, has been preserved by the right people having the right idea at the right time.  You are shaping in your hands, this very moment, the future of this company, and this nation. There is nothing else.  There’s no art opening.  There’s no benefit. There’s nothing to sign.  There’s no decisions to be made.  There’s the next mission and nothing else. There’s nothing except this.
I quit.

You’re going to kill yourself.  I can’t support that.
So far so good. Pepper.  I know what I have to do. I don’t know if I can, but I know in my heart that it’s right.  And you do too.  And I can’t do it without you.

I told you, miniaturize the ARK reactor.

Tony Stark was able to do it in a cave -- with a box of scraps.
Well...I’m not Tony Stark.

Translate--
What a nice surprise.
I...just wanted to get some of my personal stuff.  And my resume.  In case. You know how I love job hunting.
How’s Tony?
Honestly...I don’t know.  He’s shut me out.
You and everyone else.
This...thing between you, it’s hurting him.  You’re the only real father Tony ever had. It would mean so much if you could just talk --
Tony’s imploding -- it’s unfortunate.    You should consider whether you want to take that ride with him.
“Unfortunate?”
You know I love Tony -- but this is business.  We can’t save him, but we can save his legacy.
It’s tragic, but...Tony never really came home, did he?
This company has a bright future, I’d like you to be a part of it.
Tony doesn’t understand your value. He never did.
Are you...offering me a job?
Think about it.  Come on, I’ll walk you out.
Miss Potts, did you forget our appointment?
No.  Of course not.  I’ve been very much looking forward to it.  Let’s-- -- why don’t we do this somewhere else?
What gives, Jarvis?
You have a visitor, Sir.  Obadiah Stane is here.
It’s UNOS.  Four cheese.  I just had it flown in from Chicago.
I’d like you to proof-read something for me.
Would you like me to spell-check it, Sir?
Can you turn him off?  All the way?
Spin down Jarvis.
Your resignation.
You were right.  It’s not my company -- not my name on the building. We were a great team...but I guess this is where our paths diverge.
Pepper.  I should take that.
Tony.  Please.  I’ll be out of here in a minute.
We have too much history to part on bad terms.  I’d like your blessing.
Easy, now.  Try to breathe...
You can’t mess with progress, Tony. It’s an insult to the Gods.  You created your greatest weapon ever -- but you think that means it belongs to you.  It belongs to the world.
Your “heart” will be the seed of the next generation of weapons. They’ll help us steer the world back in the right direction -- put the balance of power back in our hands.  The right hands.
By the time you die, my prototype will be operational.  It’s not as conservative as yours.
The sad thing is...we’re both the good guys.
What do you mean, he paid to have Tony killed?  Slow down.  Why would Obadiah-- Where is Tony now?
--I don’t know, he’s not answering his phone.  Will you just go over there and check on him?  Thanks Rhodey.
I know a short cut.
I’ll ride with her.
Clear.
TONY--
Where’s Pepper?
Don’t worry, she’s with the Feds. They’re on their way to Stark to arrest Obadiah.
They’re going to need a lot more than a few Agents.  Give me hand.
Agents down, agents down! GET OUT OF HERE --
Tony!  Obadiah’s got a whole assembly line under the Ark.  He’s inside one of them--!
Where are you--?
Obadiah...
Tony--
Pepper, I have one thing I need to say to you:  DUCK!
It’s miraculous, Tony, it’s your Ninth Symphony.  Trying to rid the world of weapons, you gave it its best one ever.
This wasn’t meant for the world.
How can you be so selfish?  Do you understand what you’ve created? This will put the balance of power back in our hands for decades. Your country needs this.
What kind of world will it be when everybody’s got one?
Your father helped give us the bomb.  What kind of world would it be if he’d failed us?
TONY -- ARE YOU THERE?
A little busy, Pepper--
The reactor’s been it--
Get to the control room.  Shut it down--
How the hell do I shut it down??
Don’t.  This is our fight.
People are always going to die, Tony -- part of the chess game.
Emergency power!
Sir, you’ll drain the --
NOW!
GO, MOM!  GO --
TONY?  Where are you--?
I’m in the control room.  Now what?
Central panel.  Red button.  Press it.
Thanks, Tony.
What’s the delta rate?
Damn --
Damn?!  I don’t want to hear “damn.”  GET UP HERE--
Pepper, I’m delegating this to you. FIND A WAY!
You know what happens when that reactor blows.  A lot of people are going to die.
It didn’t have to end like this, Tony.  You were down -- you should’ve stayed down.
You had to take my car.
Saving your ass is getting to be a full-time job.
Get this area evacuated!  There’s going to be a meltdown--
Pepper, how we doing?
Thanks for checking in Tony. Delta’s at 2300.  It’s not going down.
It’s too late.
Too late?  What’s going to happen?
It’s going to blow a crater a mile wide.  I’m coming to get you.
Pepper, wait.  Stay put -- we’re going to overload the reactor.
IT’S ALREADY OVERLOADING --
No, it’s compressing energy.  We’re going to convert the plasma core to electricity and channel it up through the roof.  Like a Tesla coil.
I don’t need a science lesson, just tell me what button to push --
See a red submarine hatch?  A wheel -- a red wheel.
...no.  YES --
Open it all the way, then standby to hit the master.  We’ve only got one shot at this.
Pepper, hit the switch.  PEPPER --
TONY?  Which Master Switch --
I am so looking for another job.
Take my hand...
So this is the answer, Tony?  This is how you’re going to save the world?  It’s not in you.  Your father told me before he died, my boy doesn’t have a warrior’s heart. I should have listened.
My father never knew me.
But I do.
Goodbye, my boy...
This is just the beginning.
Here, your alibi.  You were on your yacht.  I’ve got port papers that put you in Avalon all night, and sworn statements from fifty of your guests.
Maybe it was just the two of us. On the yacht, I mean.
Focus, please.
“Iron Man”.  Not technically accurate, since it’s mostly carbon- fiber and ceramic.  But I like the ring of it.  “Iron Man”...
You know...that night at the concert hall.  Do you ever think about it?
I don’t know what you’re talking about, Mr. Stark.
Will that be all, Mr. Stark?
That will be all Miss Potts.

--I can confirm that a series of military test-prototypes were involved in the incident at Stark Industries last night.  I can also confirm that there was, for a brief time, the danger of an Ark Reactor “incident”, which was rectified without injury to the public -- and all power outages have been restored.  Here now, to answer a few brief questions, is Tony Stark.
I’ve seen the papers.  I’ve heard the reports.  That’s why I want to put an end to all this wild speculation.  The truth is--
I am Iron Man.
Good.  And I want a Gatling gun on the right shoulder.
--and a rocket launcher on the left?  Where are you going to store all that ammo?
Who’s suit is this anyway? And do it in silver and black, would you?
Do do do do do do do do do do do!
This way, my river lily.
Where are you taking me?
Oh. It’s beautiful.
I was afraid it wouldn’t take to the soil, but it rooted quickly.
Soon it will be everywhere - all across the universe, fulfilling life’s one true purpose.
Which is what?
Expansion.
I’m not sure what you’re talking about. But I like the way you say it.
My heart is yours, Meredith Quill.
I can’t believe I fell in love with a spaceman.
Showtime, a-holes! It’ll be here any minute!
Which will be its loss.
Is that a rifle?
You don’t know what a rifle is?
I thought your thing was a sword.
We’ve been hired to stop an interdimensional beast from feeding on those batteries’ energy, and I’m going to stop it with a sword?
Don’t look at me like I’m stupid. You’re the one being all inconsistent.
Drax, why aren’t you wearing one of Rocket’s aero-rigs?
It hurts.
Hurts?
I have sensitive nipples.
What about him?! What’s he doing?!
If I finish this, we can listen to tunes while we work.
How is that a priority?
Blame Quill! He’s the one who loves music so much!
I agree with Drax. It’s hardly important right now.
Oh, sure, okayyyy, Quill.
No, I really agree with him.
Sure, I know.
I can clearly see you winking.
Damn. I’m using my left eye?
I am Groot.
They were not looking at you funny.
Well. That’s intense.
Groot, look - !
Get out of the way, Groot! You’re going to get hurt!
Hi.
Spit it out! Spit it out!
Disgusting.
The beast’s hide is too thick to be pierced from the outside. I must cut through it from the inside.
Huh?
Drax, no! That doesn’t make -
What is he doing?!
He said the skin is too thick to be pierced from the outside, so he --
That doesn’t make sense!
I tried to tell -- !
Its skin is the same thickness from the inside as from the out!
I REALIZE THAT.
Gamora, there’s a cut on its neck - Rocket, get it to look up.
Hey, you giant Sea Monkey, up here!
Ha ha! I have single-handedly vanquished the beast!
What?
What are they called again?
Anulax batteries.
Harbulary batteries.
That’s nothing like what I just said. But they’re worth thousands of units a piece. Which is why the Sovereign hired us to protect them.
Just be careful what you say around these folks. They’re easily offended and the cost of transgression is death.
Sounds judgmental for a bunch of golden morons.
That’s the kind of thing you might want to keep to yourself.
I’ll hold my tongue, as long as they deliver what was promised.
We thank you, Guardians, for putting your life on the line. We could not risk the lives of our own Sovereign citizens.
Every citizen is born exactly as designed by the community, impeccable, both physically and mentally. We control the DNA of our progeny, germinating them in birthing pods.
I guess I prefer making people the old-fashioned way.
Well... perhaps someday you could give me a history lesson in the archaic ways of our ancestors... for academic purposes.
Yeah, I mean, if it’s for research that could be pretty --
Pretty repulsive. I’m not into that kind of casual -
Oh, please. Your people promised something in trade for our services.  Bring it and we shall gladly be on our way.
Family reunion. Yaaaay.
I understand she is your sister?
She’s worth no more to me than the bounty due for her on Xandar.
Our soldiers apprehended her attempting to steal the batteries. Do with her as you please.
Thank you, High Priestess Ayesha.
What is your heritage, Mr. Quill?
My mother is from earth.
And your father?
He’s... not from Missouri, that’s all I know.
I see it within you, an unorthodox genealogy. A hybrid that seems particularly... reckless.
You know, they told me you people were conceited douchebags. But that isn’t true at all.
Oh, shit, I’m using my wrong eye again, aren’t I? I’m sorry. That was meant to be behind your back.
Count yourself blessed they didn’t kill you.
You’re telling me. You wanna buy some batteries?
Let’s get baldy back to Xandar and retrieve that bounty!
You all right?
That stuff about my father. Who does she think she is?
I know you’re sensitive about that.
I’m not sensitive about it. I just don’t know who he is.
Sorry if it looked like I was flirting with her. I wasn’t.
I don’t care if you were.
I think you do care. That’s why I’m apologizing.
Gamora is not the one for you, Quill.
There are two types of beings in the universe. Those who dance, and those who do not.
Uh huh.
I first met my beloved at a war rally. Everyone in the village flailed about, dancing. Except one woman. My Ovette. I knew immediately she was the one.
The most melodic song in the world could be playing, and she wouldn’t even tap her foot. She wouldn’t move a muscle. One might assume she was dead.
Well, that is pretty hot, but--
It would make my nether regions engorge -
All right, okay, fascinating, don’t need to hear it.  I get your point, I’m a dancer and Gamora is not.
You just need to find a woman who is pathetic, like you.
I am hungry. Hand me some of that yaro root.
No. It’s not ripe yet. And I hate you.
You hate me?! You left me there while you stole that stone for yourself. Yet here you stand, a hero, a Garden of the Galaxy!
A what?
‘Guardians of the Galaxy.’
Oh.
Why would we be ‘the Gardens of the Galaxy’?
I don’t know. I thought it was stupid.
Yeah, it would be.
It’s still wordy.
I wasn’t the one who thought of it.
Your name doesn’t matter. I’ll be free of these shackles soon enough, and I’ll kill you, I swear.
No. You’ll live out your days in a prison on Xandar, wishing you could.
We got an armed Sovereign fleet, approaching from the rear.
Why would they do that?!
Probably because Rocket stole some of their batteries.
Dude.
Oh, right.  He didn’t steal one of those. I don’t know why they’re after us. What a mystery this is.
What were you thinking?!
Dude, it was really easy to steal.
That’s your defense?
Come on. You saw how that high- priestess talked down to us! I’m teaching her a lesson!
Oh! I didn’t realize your motivation was altruism. A shame the Sovereign have mistaken your intentions and are trying to kill us.
Exactly.
I WAS BEING SARCASTIC!
Oh no! You tricked me! You’re supposed to use a sarcastic voice! Now I look foolish!
SHUT UP, DRAX! You knew! You should have told us!
Did you tell him it was easy to steal?
Are you kidding me?
What?
You never listen to anything!
None of you listens! Can we please just put the bickering on hold until after we survive the massive space battle?!
Whoa. Somebody woke up on the wrong side of the bed this morning.
Do not try to bro down with me right now, dude.  I will fricking punch you in your fricking face.
Real nice! Resorting to violence.
More incoming!
GOOD! I WANT TO KILL SOME GUYS!
Bloody hell!
You’re not killing anyone. Those ships are all remotely piloted.
What is the delay, Admiral?
High Priestess, if we destroy their craft, we risk destroying the batteries. They’re extraordinarily combustible and could, in turn, destroy the entire fleet.
We have thousands of batteries and thousands of ships. Our concern is their slight against our people. We hired them and they steal from us? It is heresy of the highest order.
All command modules -
Fire with the intent to kill.
What’s the closest habitable planet?
It’s called Berhert.
How many jumps?
Only one. But the access point is 47 clicks away. And it’s through that Quantum Asteroid Field over there.
Quill, to make it through that, you’d have to be the greatest pilot in the universe.
Lucky for us -
I am.
What are you doing?!
I’ve been flying this rig since I was ten years old.
I was cybernetically engineered to pilot a spacecraft!
You were cybernetically engineered to be a douchebag.
Stop it!

Quill, later on tonight you’re gonna lay down in your bed and there’s gonna be something squishy in your pillowcase and you’re gonna be, like, ‘what’s this?’ and it’s gonna be because I put a turd in there.
You put your turd in my bed, I shave you.
Oh it won’t be my turd, it will be Drax’s.
I have famously huge turds.
We’re about to die, and this is what we’re discussing?
They raise havoc with the pipes. That’s why I do all the plumbing. I take responsibility for my actions. Unlike some people...
Groot, he’s right, you have to start aiming inside the box.
Stop it.
Idiots!
Well, that’s what you get when Quill flies.
Ow!
There’s still a Sovereign craft behind us!
Our weapons are down!
Twenty clicks to the jump.
Where’s he going?
Come on, Zylak, you can do this.
It’s not ripe.
Fifteen clicks.
Ten clicks.
Die, spaceship.
You suck, Zylak.
Five clicks!
Son-of-a-! They went around the field!
Someone destroyed all the ships.
What?! WHO?!
What is that?!
Doesn’t matter! That’s the jump point! GO! GO!
It’s a guy.
Oh my God.
Groot, put on your seat belt!
Prepare for a really bad -
Ow! Ow! Ow! Ow!
That was awesome.
Either one of you could have gotten us through that field, if you had flown with what’s between your ears instead of what’s between your legs!
If what’s between my legs had a hand on it, I guarantee I could have landed this ship.
It’s not funny, Peter. We almost died. Because of your arrogance.
More like because he stoled Anulax batteries!
They’re called Harbulary batteries.
No, they’re not!
You know why I did it, Star-Munch?
Do you?
I’m not going to answer to ‘Star- Munch.’
I DID IT BECAUSE I WANTED TO.
Dick.
What are we even talking about this for? We just had a little man save us by blowing up fifty ships!
How little?
Like this.
A little one-inch man saved us?
Well, if he got closer I’m sure he’d be much larger.
That’s how eyes work, you stupid raccoon.
Don’t call me a raccoon!
Oh, I’m sorry, I meant to say ‘trash panda.’
Is that better?
I don’t know.
It’s worse.
YOU SON-OF-A-!!
Someone followed you through the jump point.
Set me free.  You’ll need my help.
I’m not a fool, Nebula.
You’re a fool if you deprive yourself a hand in combat.
You’ll attack me the moment I let you go.
No, I won’t.
You’d think an evil supervillain would learn how to properly lie.
I bet it’s the one-inch man!!
After all these years, I’ve found you.
Who the hell are you?
I figured my rugged good looks would make that obvious. My name’s Ego. And I’m your Dad, Peter.
Yondu! Come on down!
And I was like, Aleta, I love you, but you’re crazy now, you always been -
Stakar.
Been some time. I’d -
Seems like this establishment is the wrong kind of disreputable.
Stakar...
There are a hundred Ravager factions, Sneeper. You just lost the business of ninety-nine by serving one.
Please, sir! Sir!
You all can go to hell! I don’t care what you think of me!
Then why you following us for?!
‘Cause you’ll listen to what I got to say!
I don’t got to listen to nothing! You betrayed the code! Ravagers don’t deal in kids!
I didn’t know what was going on -
You didn’t know ‘cause you didn’t want to know, ‘cause it made you rich!
I demand a seat at the table! I wear the flames same as you!

You may dress like a Ravager but you won’t hear no Horns of Freedom when you die, boy, and the Colors of Ogord will not flash over your grave! You think I take some pleasure in exiling you, you’re wrong. You broke all our hearts.

First Quill betrays us and Yondu just lets him go, scot-free. Now he’s getting all riled over nothing. We followed him ‘cause he was the one wasn’t afraid to do what needed to be done. Seems like he’s going soft.
If he’s so soft why you whispering for?
You know I’m right, Kraglin.
You best watch what you say about the Cap’n, Tay -
Who the hell is that?!
Yondu Udonta, I have a proposition for you.
When your mother passed away, I hired Yondu to pick you up.

I would have done so myself, but I was in the midst of an outlandish adventure at the time, battling demonic forces to save this dimension or some such nonsense - I can’t quite recall, it all bleeds together after awhile. But instead of returning you, Yondu kept you. I have no clue as to why.
Because I was a skinny kid who could squeeze into places adults couldn’t, making thieving easier.
I’ve been trying to track you down ever since.
I thought Yondu was your father.
What?
We’ve been together all this time and you thought Yondu was my actual, blood relative?
You look exactly alike.
One’s blue.
He wasn’t my father. Yondu was the guy who abducted me.  He’d beat the crap out of me so I’d learn how to fight and he kept me in terror threatening to eat me.
Eat you?!
Yes.
That son-of-a-bitch.
How’d you locate us now?
Even where I reside, out past the edge of what’s known, we’ve heard tell of the man they call Star- Lord.
Say we head out that way now? Your associates are welcome, even that triangle-faced monkey there.
I promise you, it’s like no place you’ve ever seen. And there I can explain your very special heritage, and finally be the father I’ve always wanted to be. ‘Scuse me. I gotta take a whizz.
Not buying it.
Peter, we need to take a walk.
I am Mantis.
What are you doing?
Smiling. I hear it is the thing to do to make people like you.
Not if you do it like that.
Oh. I was raised alone on Ego’s planet. I do not understand the intricacies of social interaction.
Can I pet your puppy? It is adorable.
Yes...
AHH!
That’s called a practical joke!
I liked it very much!
Give me a break! After all this time, and he just expects to be my Dad all of the sudden!
I hear you.
I mean, this could be a trap - the Kree purists, the Ravagers, now the Sovereign - they all want us dead.
I know, but -
But what?
What was that story you told me about Zardu Hasselfrau?
Who?
The wonderful television-singer man. He had a magic boat.
David Hasselhoff?
Right.
He had a talking car, not a magic -
Why did it talk again?
Just to be a good friend, I guess.
And as a child you carried his picture in your pocket, and you told the other children he was your father, but he was out of town --
Shooting Knight Rider or touring with his band in Germany. Why are you bringing this up now? I was drunk when I told you that.
I love that story.
I don’t. It’s just sad! I was so sad because I’d see the other kids off playing catch with their dads, and I wanted that, more than anything in the world.
My point is, maybe this man is your Hasselhoff. I know it’s a long shot. But I lost my father as a child. I’d give anything...
If he ends up being evil, we’ll just kill him.
What’s funny?
You’re leaving me with that fox?!
He’s not a fox.
Shoot her if she does anything suspicious. Or if you feel like it.
It will just be a couple days. We’ll be back before Rocket’s finished fixing the ship.
What about your spool of songs?
I have clones.
What if the Sovereign come?
There’s no way for them to know they’re here.
I am uncertain about parting ways.
You’re like an old woman.
Because I am wise?
Hope daddy isn’t as big of a dick as you, orphan boy.
So what’s your goal here? To get everyone to hate you? ‘Cause it’s working.
Can I ask you a personal question?
Oh, no one has ever asked me a personal question!
The antennae, what are they for?
Their purpose?
Yes, Quill and I have a bet.
You’re not supposed to say that.
I say that if you are about to go through a doorway that is too low, your antennae will feel this, and stop you from being decapitated.
Just making clear - if it’s anything else - any other answer - I win?
They are not for feeling doorways.
Damn. I just lost my entire life’s savings.
Three pairs of pants.
I think they have something to do with my empathic abilities.
What are - ?
If I touch someone I can feel their feelings -
You read minds?
No. Telepaths know thoughts. Empaths feel feelings. Emotions.
May I?
You feel love.
Yeah, I guess, yeah, I have sort of a general, unselfish love for everyone.
No, romantic, sexual love.
No. No, I don’t.
For her.
No.
She just told everyone your deepest, darkest secret, Quill! HAHAHAHAHAHA!!!
What the hell, dude? That’s a total overreaction.
DO ME! DO ME!
I have never felt such humor!
You got to be kidding me.
That’s so incredibly uncool.
Touch me. And the only thing you’re going to feel is a broken jaw.
I can also alter emotions, to some extent.
Like what?

If I touch someone who is sad I can ease them into contentment, for a short while. I can make a stubborn person compliant. But I mostly use it to help my Master sleep. He lies awake at night, thinking about his progeny.
Do one of those on me!
Sleep.
Is that real?
It’s kind of like someone put a baby’s head on a big, muscular body, isn’t it?
There!
Ain’t so tough now without all your toys, are you?
Crap.
Hey there, rat.
How’s it going, you blue idiot?
Eh, not so bad. We got a pretty good gig. A golden gal with quite a high opinion of herself offered us a large sum to deliver you and your pals to her, so she can kill y’all.
Your friend. There’s too many of them. They’re going to kill him.
He needs my help. If you care about him, you need to get me out of these bonds.
Pretty easy to find you, since we put a tracer on your ship back during the War over Xandar.
You give me your word you won’t hurt Groot, and I’ll tell you where the batteries are.
Lucky for you my word don’t mean squat. Otherwise I’d actually hand you over.
Otherwise you’d what?!
We’ll take the batteries. They’re worth a a quarter mil on the open market -
That priestess offered us a million! A quarter is only one third of that!
A quarter ain’t one-th -
A quarter is four times a million! We’re in the money!
No, idiot. A quarter is twenty- five.
No -
We can’t even buy a pair of boots with twenty-five units!
The point is, we aren’t stupid enough to help kill the Guardians of the Galaxy. We’d have the whole Nova Corps on us.
That ain’t right. I just gotta say it this one time, Cap’n.
No matter how many times Quill betrays you, you protect him, like none of the rest of us much matter. I’m the one what sticks up for you, me and Tullk.
Damn straight, lad. You’re right: he’s going soft. S’pose it’s time for a change in leadership!
Uh -
Put you damn guns down!
Hold on! There’s got to be some sort of peaceful resolution here! Or even a violent resolution, where I’m standing over there.
Well, hello, boys.
It’s not ripe.
Welcome, friends, to my world.
Wow. You have your own planet?
But a trifle, no larger than your earth’s moon.
Humility. I like it. I too, am extraordinarily humble.
It’s beautiful.
Peter, consider this a token of a father’s pride.
A memorial to the War Over Xandar, when you single-handedly saved the galaxy.
Single-handedly?
Whoa. It’s perfect.
You’ve got to be kidding.
Why am I dead? Why did you all kill me?!
That’s Ronan. That’s you.
When was I that tiny?
You own a planet and can destroy two dozen spaceships without a suit. What are you, exactly?
I’m what they call a Celestial, sweetheart.
A Celestial. Like a... god?
Small ‘g’, son. At least on the days I’m feeling humble as Drax.
This form you see before you is only an extension of who I truly am. I don’t know where I came from, exactly.
The first thing I remember is flickering, adrift in the cosmos - utterly and entirely alone.
I fed on the matter around me like plankton. I grew smarter and stronger.
I formed a sheathe to protect myself from the elements.
And continued building from there, layer by layer, the very planet you walk on now. I built the spires reaching up to the sky and the tunnels burrowing into its depths.
Wow.
But I was no ant to be fulfilled solely by labor. I wanted more. I desired... meaning.
There must be some life out there in the universe besides just me, I thought, and I set myself to task with finding it.
I created what I imagined biological life might be like, down to the most minute detail.
Did you make a penis?
Dude.
If he’s a planet, how did he make a baby with your mother? He would smush her.
I don’t need to hear about how my parents, you know -
Why? My father would tell me the story of impregnating my mother every winter solstice.
That’s disgusting.
It was beautiful. You earthers have hang-ups.
Yes, Drax, I’ve got a penis.
Oh my God.
It’s not half bad. I’ve also got pain receptors, a digestive system, and all the accompanying junk. I wanted to experience what it truly meant to be human as I set out amongst the stars.

Life. I was not alone in this universe after all.

Peter -

Disgusting?

Just watching the fireworks.
Gamora, let her go!

You are scared.

Over thousands of years I implanted thousands of extensions of myself on thousands of worlds.
I needed to fulfill life’s one true purpose: to grow and to spread, covering all that exists, until everything... is me.
What did she do to me?!
She already told me everything.

Out of all my labors the most beguiling was attempting to graft my DNA with that of another species. I hoped the result of such a coupling would be enough to power the expansion.
I had Yondu deliver some of them to me. It broke the Ravager code - but I compensated him generously. And, to ease his conscience, I told him I would never hurt them.

Forever.

Temporary.

Cap’n?
